comments.body:
There's this for material widgets https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/MaterialTapTargetSize-class.html. It's used to identify widgets that should be atleast 48x48.

There's this for tests: https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/flutter_test/MinimumTapTargetGuideline-class.html. The value of androidTapTargetGuideline is 48x48, for iOSTapTargetGuideline it's 44x44.

This set of mostly private constants are probably more of the same:

```
flutter/lib/src/material/paginated_data_table.dart:    this.dataRowHeight = 48.0,
flutter/lib/src/material/expansion_panel.dart:const double _kPanelHeaderCollapsedHeight = 48.0;
flutter/lib/src/material/range_slider.dart:  static const double _minTouchTargetWidth = 48;
flutter/lib/src/material/icon_button.dart:const double _kMinButtonSize = 48.0;
flutter/lib/src/material/data_table.dart:    this.dataRowHeight = 48.0,
flutter/lib/src/material/dropdown.dart:const double _kMenuItemHeight = 48.0;
flutter/lib/src/material/popup_menu.dart:const double _kMenuItemHeight = 48.0;
flutter/lib/src/material/constants.dart:const double kTextTabBarHeight = 48.0;
flutter/lib/src/widgets/text_selection.dart:const double kMinInteractiveSize = 48.0;
```

```
flutter/lib/src/cupertino/button.dart:    this.minSize = 44.0,
flutter/lib/src/cupertino/nav_bar.dart:const double _kNavBarPersistentHeight = 44.0;
flutter/lib/src/material/text_selection.dart:const double _kToolbarHeight = 44.0;
```

In a separate PR we should probably create a pair of constants and update this stuff. Including the _kMinInteractiveSize constant added here.

